\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 * {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.linkedin.com/company/anthropicresearch/"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \strokec4 Anthropic}} analyzed ~1 million agent tool calls. Software engineering accounts for 50%. Back-office automation? 9%.\cb1 \
\ls1\ilvl0\cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 * {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.linkedin.com/in/maxlevchin/"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \strokec4 Max Levchin}} posted (on X) that most S&P 500 companies would love to build their own software but can't find the engineering talent. True...I've witnessed this.\cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 \
