\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 We explored what an age of abundance might look like:\cb1 \
\ls1\ilvl0\cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 1\uc0\u65039 \u8419  AI & Robots \'97 When intelligence exists everywhere \'97 digital and robotics \'97 what gets unlocked? Productivity? Creativity? Or entirely new civilizations?\cb1 \
\ls1\ilvl0\cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 2\uc0\u65039 \u8419  Food \'97 Can genetics and cellular biology finally make food abundant, affordable, and climate-proof?\cb1 \
\ls1\ilvl0\cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 3\uc0\u65039 \u8419  Longevity \'97 Epigenetics, not supplements. Could reprogramming our cells (think, Yamanaka factors) allow us to live healthy lives to 150 \'97 maybe even 200?\cb1 \
\ls1\ilvl0\cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 4\uc0\u65039 \u8419  Energy \'97 With sustained fusion being actively worked on, are we just a few decades away from near-infinite, near-free energy?\cb1 \
